---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Hidden Gems of Scripture — Nazaryah"
  description="Discoveries that emerge only when you read the original text — passages that reward the careful reader with something no commentary ever told you."
>
  <section style="background: #0a0702; padding: 4rem 1.5rem 5rem; border-top: 1px solid #2a1e0c;">
    <div style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto;">

      <p style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 4px; text-transform: uppercase; color: #BA7517; text-align: center; margin-bottom: 0.6rem;">&#8213; Featured Gem &#8213;</p>
      <h1 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.6rem); font-weight: 700; color: #f0e0bf; text-align: center; margin: 0 0 0.75rem;">Hidden Gems of Scripture</h1>
      <p style="font-size: 1rem; color: #a89f8c; font-style: italic; text-align: center; max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto 3rem; line-height: 1.7;">
        Discoveries that emerge only when you read the original text — passages that reward the careful reader with something no commentary ever told you.
      </p>

      <div class="gems-grid" style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 1.5rem;">

        <!-- Card 1: Psalm 119 -->
        <a href="/hebrew/psalm-119" style="text-decoration: none; display: block; background: #130e06; border: 1px solid #3a2510; border-left: 3px solid #BA7517; border-radius: 6px; padding: 1.75rem; transition: background 0.2s, border-color 0.2s;" onmouseover="this.style.background='#1a1007'; this.style.borderColor='#BA7517';" onmouseout="this.style.background='#130e06'; this.style.borderColor='#3a2510'; this.style.borderLeftColor='#BA7517';">
          <div style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 3px; text-transform: uppercase; color: #BA7517; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">&#10022; Study</div>
          <div style="display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;" dir="rtl">
            <span style="font-size: 1.8rem; color: #6a4820; line-height: 1;">𐤕𐤄𐤋𐤉𐤌</span>
            <span style="font-size: 1.4rem; color: #c4a46b; line-height: 1;">תהילים</span>
          </div>
          <h3 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 700; color: #f0e0bf; margin: 0 0 0.25rem;">The Message Within the Message</h3>
          <div style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 1.5px; text-transform: uppercase; color: #6a4820; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Psalm 119</div>
          <p style="font-size: 0.88rem; color: #a89f8c; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">Five discoveries hidden inside the 22 sentences of Psalm 119 — the architecture of the journey, the first and last, the Aleph-Tav, the declaration of Yahushua, and the plain verdict. Each one a gem that has waited three thousand years to be seen together.</p>
          <div style="margin-top: 1.25rem; font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 1.5px; text-transform: uppercase; color: #BA7517;">Enter Study &#8594;</div>
        </a>

        <!-- Card 2: The Beat and the Melody -->
        <a href="/blog/the-beat-and-the-melody" style="text-decoration: none; display: block; background: #130e06; border: 1px solid #3a2510; border-left: 3px solid #BA7517; border-radius: 6px; padding: 1.75rem; transition: background 0.2s, border-color 0.2s;" onmouseover="this.style.background='#1a1007'; this.style.borderColor='#BA7517';" onmouseout="this.style.background='#130e06'; this.style.borderColor='#3a2510'; this.style.borderLeftColor='#BA7517';">
          <div style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 3px; text-transform: uppercase; color: #BA7517; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">&#10022; Study</div>
          <div style="display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
            <span style="font-size: 1.8rem; color: #c4a46b; line-height: 1;">תֹּף</span>
            <span style="font-size: 1.2rem; color: #6a4820; line-height: 1;">◆</span>
            <span style="font-size: 1.8rem; color: #c4a46b; line-height: 1;">כִּנּוֹר</span>
          </div>
          <h3 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 700; color: #f0e0bf; margin: 0 0 0.25rem;">The Beat and the Melody</h3>
          <div style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 1.5px; text-transform: uppercase; color: #6a4820; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Toph &amp; Kinnor · Flesh &amp; Spirit</div>
          <p style="font-size: 0.88rem; color: #a89f8c; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">Two instruments, two realms. The tambourine beats in the body and lives in time; the harp vibrates in the spirit realm and is the only instrument named in heaven. A hidden map of flesh and spirit written into the music of Scripture.</p>
          <div style="margin-top: 1.25rem; font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 1.5px; text-transform: uppercase; color: #BA7517;">Read the Study &#8594;</div>
        </a>

        <!-- Card 3: Fate and Fortune (Gad and Meni) -->
        <a href="/blog/fate-and-fortune" style="text-decoration: none; display: block; background: #130e06; border: 1px solid #3a2510; border-left: 3px solid #BA7517; border-radius: 6px; padding: 1.75rem; transition: background 0.2s, border-color 0.2s;" onmouseover="this.style.background='#1a1007'; this.style.borderColor='#BA7517';" onmouseout="this.style.background='#130e06'; this.style.borderColor='#3a2510'; this.style.borderLeftColor='#BA7517';">
          <div style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 3px; text-transform: uppercase; color: #BA7517; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">&#10022; Study</div>
          <div style="display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
            <span style="font-size: 1.8rem; color: #c4a46b; line-height: 1;">גַּד</span>
            <span style="font-size: 1.2rem; color: #6a4820; line-height: 1;">◆</span>
            <span style="font-size: 1.8rem; color: #c4a46b; line-height: 1;">מְנִי</span>
          </div>
          <h3 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 700; color: #f0e0bf; margin: 0 0 0.25rem;">Fate and Fortune</h3>
          <div style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 1.5px; text-transform: uppercase; color: #6a4820; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Gad &amp; Meni · Isaiah 65:11</div>
          <p style="font-size: 0.88rem; color: #a89f8c; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">Two Hebrew names the KJV buried as "troop" and "number" are actually the pagan gods of Fortune and Fate. Trace them from Isaiah's counterfeit communion table to Belshazzar's wall, to the casino, the wheel, and the cartoons still selling the same religion.</p>
          <div style="margin-top: 1.25rem; font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 1.5px; text-transform: uppercase; color: #BA7517;">Read the Study &#8594;</div>
        </a>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    @media (max-width: 640px) {
      .gems-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr !important; }
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
